      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on my dissertation data and i'm a bit stuck with the interpretation. if i get a p-value of 0.06, how do i formally explain why it's considered \"not statistically significant\" even if the effect size looks pretty high? i want to make sure i'm not being too dismissive of the trend but also staying mathematically sound.",
