      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait sorry \"academic goblins\"? i didnt quite catch that lol. anyway, back to the stats—when i'm writing this up, how do i address the \"noise\" in the data? i feel like there's a lot of random variance making it hard to hit that 0.05 mark. is there a professional way to describe that interference without sounding like the study just failed?",
